        "header": "1Introduction",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.30931/2605.30931v1/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Overview ofMineExplorer. We first construct atomic task sets by separating open-world knowledge from Minecraft-specific priors, and then map the retained tasks to various capabilities. We further synthesize implicit multi-hop tasks and instantiate them with a multi-agent workflow for benchmark construction. The resulting benchmark places agents in dynamic environments and evaluates their progress with rule-based milestone checks.",
                "position": 358
            }
        ]
